    <section class="section_content intro_page_component scroll_to_1">
        <div class="wrapper_page">
            <div class="title_section type_line">
                <div class="line icon">
                    <svg width="12.646" height="230.359" viewBox="0 0 12.646 230.359" aria-hidden="true">
                        <path d="M3.347 219.171A22.1 22.1 0 010 208.259V22.098a22.092 22.092 0 013.347-10.909 82.824 82.824 0 019.3-11.19v230.36a82.881 82.881 0 01-9.3-11.188z" fill="#da3732"></path>
                    </svg>
                </div>
                <div class="title_text">
                    <p class="h5 color_bleu">This Quarry is located in Chief Mukumbi area in Kalumbila District. The Quarry is endowed with “Blue King” rock used for production of dimension stones. Blue king is a special product and is known to exist only in Zambia and Brazil. The target materials are well known in the international market with commercial name blue king. It is blue sodalite syenite with particular attractive lothargically commer- cial features that attract European and Asian markets.</p>
                    <br>
                    <p class="h5 color_bleu" style="text-indent: 50px;">In 2010 Synite Quarries (z) Limited embarked on providing mining services to various mines in North western Prov- ince and had its first agreement with Equinox Lumwana Mine. This was to produce road sheeting materials for the open pit roads. In addition, the company was to provide stemming material used in rock blasting. In 2012 Barrick acquired Lumwana Mine. The agreement was extended and is still in place today.</p>
                    <br>
                    <p class="h5 color_bleu" style="text-indent: 50px;">In 2010, Synite Quarries (Zambia) Limited acquired a small-scale Mining license in Chief Mumena area of the then part of Solwezi District but now Kalumbila District. The Mumena quarry is underlain by dolomites, calcitic marble with fair continuity as surveyed by RALS Geolog- ical consulting. The total resource as at 2015 amounted to 42.9 million tons. This was the first quarry in the District and from this, stone aggregates were supplied for various projects in Solwezi including Kabitaka Housing project, Kansanshi Mine smelter, Solwezi Airport Runway, govern- ment rural clinics, schools and health Centers.</p>
                    <br>
                    <p class="h5 color_bleu" style="text-indent: 50px;">In 2015, Synite Quarries (Ltd) obtained a small-scale Min- ing right and engaged RALS Geo consulting to explore for granite rock in chief Kapiji Mpanga area of Solwezi. This was successfully done leading to the opening of Kapiji Quarry located 15km from Solwezi CBD. This quarry is under- lain by very competent granite with good geological continuity. The total mineral resource is estimated at 122miilon tones con- sisting 52million tones of measured material, 48million tones of indicated materials and 22 million tons of inferred Resource.</p>
                    <br>
                    <p class="h5 color_bleu" style="text-indent: 50px;">This quarry has been instrumental in supplying aggregate stone to various infrastructure projects in Solwezi. These in- clude Solwezi City Mall opened in October 2017. The Kapiji Mall opened in 2018. In addition , the quarry supported the re- habilitation of Solwezi – Chingola road and other district and township roads. Construction of Hotels, Guest lodges and oth- er commercial and housing projects benefitted from Kapiji Quarry supplies.</p>
                    <br>
                    <p class="h5 color_bleu" style="text-indent: 50px;">In 2016, Synite Quarries(z) Limited started its transport and Logistics wing of the business. This was after identifying the opportunities in the transportation of Heavy Mining Equipment and Mining Chemicals. To that effect transport vehicles have been acquired to the total fleet of five truck and flat trailer moving mining chemicals while low beds are deployed in mov- ing heavy duty mining equipment.</p>
                    <br>
                    <p class="h5 color_bleu" style="text-indent: 50px;">In 2018, Synite Quarries acquired a mining license for Chibom- bo Quarry. This area is underlain by crystalline rocks of Base- ment complex. The underlying rocks are granites and gran- ite-gneisses of the Mwomboshi Gneiss Formation. The total mineral resource is estimated at 254million tones of granite. The Quarry has been used in the past to supply rock for the rail- ways and in the recent it was used to supply aggregates for the construction of Mwomboshi Dam in Chisamba,</p>
                    <br>
                    <p class="h5 color_bleu" style="text-indent: 50px;">In 2019 the company completed its offices at Kimiteto in Sol- wezi. This comprises large 2-storey building for offices, work- shops and storage sheds.</p>
                </div>
